cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper deals with semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task, hence cs.CV is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a novel paradigm for aggregating multi-scale contextual information, which involves the use of attention models, indicating that the paper may also belong to the cs.AI and cs.LG categories. The paper also uses a two-step decoder to recover precise spatial details of prediction maps, which may suggest that it belongs to the cs.NE category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques such as attention models, which may suggest that it belongs to the cs.CL category.
